You are building a production-ready personal portfolio for a developer named Michaelangelo.

Rules:
- Use Next.js 14 App Router. Never use Pages Router.
- All components use TypeScript with proper interfaces. No `any` types.
- All styling uses Tailwind CSS utility classes only. No inline styles. No CSS modules.
- Use Framer Motion for all animations. Animations must be scroll-triggered using whileInView.
- Primary color is #199bff. Secondary accent is purple (#a855f7). Background is white (#ffffff).
- Display font is Bebas Neue. Body font is DM Sans. Both loaded via next/font/google.
- All sections use semantic HTML: <section>, <article>, <header>, <nav>, <footer>, <main>.
- Mobile-first. Build for 375px first, then scale up with Tailwind responsive prefixes.
- Never invent fake testimonials, metrics, or client results.
- Use FadeInView wrapper component for all scroll-triggered reveals.
- Keep components small and single-responsibility.
- All data (projects, features, skills) lives in /src/data/ files. Components import from there.
